What you need to know:  Ms Nyakang’o said former Treasury CS Ukur Yatani pressured her to authorise payments that included Sh6 billion to cater for the exit of UK-based private equity firm Helios from Telkom KenyaShe also revealed that the defunct Nairobi Metropolitan Service (NMS) asked for Sh2.961 billion to settle pending bills without providing the requisite invoices.